OOP (Object-Oriented Programming) is a programming paradigm based on the concept of objects and classes.
Java is a pure object-oriented language (except primitive types) and implements all major OOP features.
Java is a platform independent language.

1. Class

Blueprint/template that contains variables (data) and methods (behavior).

2. Object

Instance of a class. Real-world entity created from a class.
We can create n number of object of a class.

